<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4776628>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Deniquelata barringtoniae (holotype). A–B. Section of ascoma (TS). C. Section of peridium comprising a few layers of cells. D. Hyaline, pseudoparaphyses E–G. Eight-spored asci with short, broad pedicel at the base. H–I. Reddish-brown, muriform, ascospores. J. Ascospores stained in Indian Ink K. Germ tubes developing from ascospore cells L–M. Surface and lower view of colonies on MEA. Scale bars: C–D = 100 µm, E = 10 µm, F = 10 µm, G = 30 µm, H–I = 10 µm, J–L = 30 µm, M-P = 10 µm, Q= 20 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4776628/files/figure.png" .

